{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2013}} '''Aaron del Valle''', a Chicago Police officer, was a member of the [[Hispanic Democratic Organization]] (HDO), a [[political action committee]] (PAC), officially started in 1993, to aid political power for the Hispanic community in Chicago and throughout [[Illinois]].
== 2007 election campaign == Aaron del Valle was a candidate for the office of 25th Ward Alderman of Chicago on February 27, 2007. He was one of five candidates vying to unseat the current Alderman [[Daniel Solis]]. During the campaign, Aaron del Valle did not make any public appearances regarding his candidacy. He did receive 329 votes placing him in 5th place with 4.8% of the total vote.<ref>[http://chicagoelections.com/wdlevel3.asp?elec_code=65 Online election tallies<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927225058/http://chicagoelections.com/wdlevel3.asp?elec_code=65 |date=September 27, 2007 }}</ref>
