== Controversies == In 2006, a Federal investigation was launched into hiring practices at [[Chicago City Hall]]. HDO and other political groups allegedly have had influence over the city's hiring system and political workers allegedly have been rewarded with city jobs and promotions.
Aaron del Valle is alleged to have assisted [[Al Sanchez]], an [[Hispanic Democratic Organization|HDO]] leader, in coordinating HDO activities and was charged with perjury for allegedly lying to the federal grand jury about his HDO activities.<ref>[http://cbs2chicago.com/topstories/aaron.del.valle.2.336064.html cbs2chicago.com - Former Top Daley Aide Indicted For Fraud<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081012062358/http://cbs2chicago.com/topstories/aaron.del.valle.2.336064.html |date=October 12, 2008 }}</ref> Del Valle was considered Sanchez's lieutenant in the HDO organization.
