'''Rectitis''' is an inflammation of the inner [[rectum]]. It mainly affects the rectal [[mucous membrane]].<ref name="ccm.net"/>  The condition can be acute or it may be a chronic condition. Rectitis may be caused due to conditions such as [[ulcerative colitis]] or [[Chron's disease]].<ref name="ccm.net">{{cite web|url=http://health.ccm.net/faq/2378-rectitis-definition|title=Rectitis - Definition|website=CCM Health}}</ref>

