{{Infobox language |name=Solombala-English |region=[[Solombala]], [[Arkhangelsk]], [[Russia]] |extinct=Late 19th century |familycolor=Pidgin |family=[[English pidgin|English]]–[[Russian language|Russian]] [[pidgin]] |script=[[Russian alphabet]] |iso3=none |glotto=solo1261 |glottorefname=Solombala English }}
'''Solombala-English''', or '''Solombala English–Russian Pidgin''', is a little-known [[pidgin]], derived from both [[English language|English]] and [[Russian language|Russian]], that was spoken in the port of [[Solombala]] in the neighborhood of [[Arkhangelsk]] (Archangel), [[Russia]] in the 18th and 19th centuries.
The known Solombala-English corpus consists of only two short 19th-century texts: one in ''Очерки Архангельской губерний'' (Sketches from the district of Archangel) by Vasilij Vereščagin from 1849, and one in ''Архангельские Губернские Ведомости'' (Archangel District News) from 1867. __NOTOC__ ==References== ===Primary sources=== *{{cite news |author=Prušakevič, Ivan |year=1867 |script-title=ru:Соломбала зимою а летом |work=Архангельские Губернские Ведомости |page=85 |language=Russian}} *{{cite book |author=Vereščagin, Vasilij |year=1849 |script-title=ru:Очерки Архангельской губерний |location=Saint Petersburg |publisher=Jakov Trej |language=Russian}}
