'''Tacho''' is an indigenous ethnic group of [[South Sudan]] based mainly around southern [[Kurdufan|Kordofan]] and in the Moro Hills<ref name=josh>{{cite web|title=Moro Hills of Sudan|url=http://www.joshuaproject.net/people-profile.php?peo3=13818&rog3=SU|publisher=www.joshuaproject.net|accessdate=9 September 2012}}</ref>  and in the areas surrounding the border between [[Sudan]] and [[South Sudan]]. They are also known by the names Tocho and Toicho;<ref name=ethno>{{cite web|title=Tocho A Language of Sudan|url=http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=taz|publisher=www.ethnologue.com|accessdate=9 September 2012}}</ref> about 90% of the population practice [[Islam]]<ref name="ethno"/>  as their main religion.

They speak [[Tocho language|Tocho]],<ref name="ethno"/> which is of the [[Talodi people|Talodi]] language group, with its root in the [[Niger-Congo languages]]. However they also speak [[Sudanese Arabic]]. Today their population possibly numbers less than 10,000.

